Bishopric of Cammin.label: Bishopric of Cammin
Bishopric of Cammin.description: The Bishopric of Cammin was both a former Roman Catholic diocese in the Duchy of Pomerania from 1140 to 1544, and a secular territory in the Kolberg area from 1248 to 1650. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of Pittsburgh.label: Episcopal Diocese of Pittsburgh
Episcopal Diocese of Pittsburgh.description: The Episcopal Diocese of Pittsburgh is a diocese in the Episcopal Church in the United States of America. Geographically, it encompasses several counties in Western Pennsylvania, and its cathedral is located in downtown Pittsburgh. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Passau.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Passau
Roman Catholic Diocese of Passau.description: The Diocese of Passau is a Roman Catholic diocese in Germany that is a suffragan of the Archdiocese of Munich and Freising. Wikipedia

Diocese of Härnösand.label: Diocese of Härnösand
Diocese of Härnösand.description: The Diocese of Härnösand is a division in the Church of Sweden in Västernorrland County. The Cathedral is located at Trädgårdsgatan in Härnösand. Wikipedia

Diocese of Gothenburg.label: Diocese of Gothenburg
Diocese of Gothenburg.description: The diocese of Gothenburg is a diocese of the Church of Sweden. Since September, 2011 the Bishop has been Per Eckerdal. 1949–1970 it was Bo Giertz. The diocese includes the provinces of Bohuslän, Halland, and south-west parts of Västergötland. Wikipedia

Apostolic Vicariate of Paksé.label: Apostolic Vicariate of Paksé
Apostolic Vicariate of Paksé.description: Vicariate Apostolic of Paksé is a major unit of the Roman Catholic Church in Laos. The Vicar Apostolic since 2000 is Louis-Marie Ling Mangkhanekhoun. It was established in 1967, when it was split off from the Vicariate Apostolic of Savannakhet. Wikipedia

Diocese of Linköping.label: Diocese of Linköping
Diocese of Linköping.description: The Diocese of Linköping is a diocese within the Church of Sweden administering the Östergötland County, the north eastern part of Jönköping County and the northern part of Kalmar County. Wikipedia

Diocese of Lund.label: Diocese of Lund
Diocese of Lund.description: The Diocese of Lund is the southernmost diocese in the Church of Sweden. The territory of the diocese corresponds to the provinces of Blekinge and Scania. Wikipedia

Diocese of Växjö.label: Diocese of Växjö
Diocese of Växjö.description: The Diocese of Växjö is one of the 13 dioceses or regional units of the Lutheran Church of Sweden. It was also a former Roman Catholic bishopric. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ibagué.label: Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ibagué
Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ibagué.description: The Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ibagué is an archdiocese located in the city of Ibagué in Colombia. Wikipedia

Diocese of Strängnäs.label: Diocese of Strängnäs
Diocese of Strängnäs.description: The Diocese of Strängnäs is a part of the Church of Sweden and has its seat in Strängnäs Cathedral in Strängnäs, south of Lake Mälaren. The diocese is made up of the two provinces Närke and Södermanland. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Gualeguaychú.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Gualeguaychú
Roman Catholic Diocese of Gualeguaychú.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Gualeguaychú is in Argentina and is a suffragan of the Archdiocese of Paraná. Wikipedia

Diocese of Karlstad.label: Diocese of Karlstad
Diocese of Karlstad.description: The Diocese of Karlstad is a diocese of the Church of Sweden. It covers most of the provinces Värmland and Dalsland. Its current borders are from 1693. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Líbano–Honda.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Líbano–Honda
Roman Catholic Diocese of Líbano–Honda.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Líbano–Honda is a diocese located in the cities of Líbano and Honda in the Ecclesiastical province of Ibagué in Colombia. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orlean.label: Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orleans
Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orlean.description: The Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orleans, officially in Latin Archidioecesis Novae Aureliae, is an ecclesiastical division of the Roman Catholic Church administered from New Orleans, Louisiana. Wikipedia

Diocese of Møre.label: Diocese of Møre
Diocese of Møre.description: The Diocese of Møre is a diocese in the Church of Norway which geographically consists of Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. Its bishop is seated at the Molde Cathedral which is located in the county administrative center of Molde. Wikipedia

Territorial Abbey of Monte Oliveto Maggi.label: Territorial Abbey of Monte Oliveto Maggiore
Territorial Abbey of Monte Oliveto Maggi.description: The Abbey of Monte Oliveto Maggiore is a large Benedictine monastery in the Italian region of Tuscany, 10 km south of Asciano. Wikipedia

Military Ordinariate of the Philippines.label: Military Ordinariate of the Philippines
Military Ordinariate of the Philippines.description: The Military Ordinariate of the Philippines or MOP is a personal diocese for the Armed Forces of the Philippines, Philippine National Police, and the Philippine Coast Guard. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of Atlanta.label: Episcopal Diocese of Atlanta
Episcopal Diocese of Atlanta.description: The Episcopal Diocese of Atlanta is the diocese of the Episcopal Church in the United States of America, with jurisdiction over middle and north Georgia. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Bragança do Pa.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Bragança do Pará
Roman Catholic Diocese of Bragança do Pa.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Bragança do Pará is a diocese located in the city of Bragança do Pará in the Ecclesiastical province of Belém do Pará in Brazil. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Coria-Cáceres.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Coria-Cáceres
Roman Catholic Diocese of Coria-Cáceres.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Coria-Cáceres is a diocese located in the cities of Coria and Cáceres in the Ecclesiastical province of Mérida–Badajoz in Spain. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Humaitá.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Humaitá
Roman Catholic Diocese of Humaitá.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Humaitá is a diocese located in the city of Humaitá in the Ecclesiastical province of Porto Velho in Brazil. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Málaga–Soatá.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Málaga–Soatá
Roman Catholic Diocese of Málaga–Soatá.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Málaga–Soatá is a diocese located in the cities of Málaga and Soatá in the Ecclesiastical province of Bucaramanga in Colombia. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of São José dos C.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of São José dos Campos
Roman Catholic Diocese of São José dos C.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of São José dos Campos is a diocese located in the city of São José dos Campos in the Ecclesiastical province of Aparecida in Brazil. Wikipedia

Dolia (titular see).label: Dolia
Dolia (titular see).description: Dolia is a Catholic titular see in Sardinia, Italy, instituted in 1969. The diocese with see at Dolia, now Dolianova, in Sardinia was suppressed in 1503, its territory going to the diocese of Cagliari. Wikipedia

Diocese of Wakefield.label: Diocese of Wakefield
Diocese of Wakefield.description: The Diocese of Wakefield is a Church of England diocese based in Wakefield in West Yorkshire, covering Wakefield, Barnsley, Kirklees and Calderdale. The cathedral is Wakefield Cathedral and the bishop is the Bishop of Wakefield. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of South Dakota.label: Episcopal Diocese of South Dakota
Episcopal Diocese of South Dakota.description: The Episcopal Diocese of South Dakota is a diocese of the Episcopal Church with jurisdiction over the state of South Dakota. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Mainz.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Mainz
Roman Catholic Diocese of Mainz.description: The Diocese of Mainz is a diocese of the Catholic church in Germany, historically known in English by its French name of Mayence. It was created in 1802 with the abolition of the old Archbishopric of Mainz. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Dublin.label: Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Dublin
Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Dublin.description: The Archdiocese of Dublin, is a Roman Catholic archdiocese in eastern Ireland centred around the republic's capital city – Dublin. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Birmingham in.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Birmingham in Alabama
Roman Catholic Diocese of Birmingham in.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Birmingham in Alabama is a particular church of the Latin Rite of the Roman Catholic Church that encompasses the northern 39 counties of the U.S. state of Alabama. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of Northern Indiana.label: Episcopal Diocese of Northern Indiana
Episcopal Diocese of Northern Indiana.description: The Episcopal Diocese of Northern Indiana, originally called the Episcopal Diocese of Michigan City, is the diocese of the Episcopal Church in the United States of America with jurisdiction over the northern one-third of Indiana. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of Eastern Michigan.label: Episcopal Diocese of Eastern Michigan
Episcopal Diocese of Eastern Michigan.description: The Episcopal Diocese of Eastern Michigan is the Episcopal diocese in the northern two-thirds of the eastern half of the Lower Peninsula of Michigan, not including the greater Detroit area, which is in the Episcopal Diocese of Michigan. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of West Missouri.label: Episcopal Diocese of West Missouri
Episcopal Diocese of West Missouri.description: The Episcopal Diocese of West Missouri, is the diocese of the Episcopal Church in the United States of America with jurisdiction over western Missouri. Wikipedia

Episcopal Diocese of East Carolina.label: The Episcopal Diocese of East Carolina

Roman Catholic Diocese of Broken Bay.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Broken Bay
Roman Catholic Diocese of Broken Bay.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Broken Bay is a suffragan Latin Rite diocese of the Archdiocese of Sydney, covering the North Shore and Northern Beaches of greater metropolitan Sydney, and the Broken Bay ... Wikipedia

Diocese of Niagara.label: Diocese of Niagara
Diocese of Niagara.description: The Diocese of Niagara is one of thirty regional divisions in the Anglican Church of Canada. The see city of the diocese is Hamilton with the Bishop's seat being located at Christ's Church Cathedral on James Street North. Wikipedia

Diocese of Qu'Appelle.label: Diocese of Qu'Appelle
Diocese of Qu'Appelle.description: The Diocese of Qu'Appelle in the Anglican Church of Canada lies in the southern third of the civil province of Saskatchewan and contains within its geographical boundaries some 50% of the province's population of one million. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Cork and Ross.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Cork and Ross
Roman Catholic Diocese of Cork and Ross.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Cork and Ross is a Roman Catholic diocese in southern Ireland. It is one of six suffragan dioceses in the ecclesiastical province of Cashel and is subject to the Archdiocese of Cashel and Emly. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Bielsko–Żywiec.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Bielsko–Żywiec
Roman Catholic Diocese of Bielsko–Żywiec.description: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Bielsko–Żywiec is a diocese located in the cities of Bielsko and Żywiec in the Ecclesiastical province of Kraków in Poland. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Waterford and.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Waterford and Lismore
Roman Catholic Diocese of Waterford and.description: The Diocese of Waterford and Lismore is a Roman Catholic diocese in southern Ireland. It is one of six suffragan dioceses in the ecclesiastical province of Cashel and is subject to the Archbishop of Cashel and Emly. Wikipedia

Roman Catholic Diocese of Raphoe.label: Roman Catholic Diocese of Raphoe
Roman Catholic Diocese of Raphoe.description: The Diocese of Raphoe is a Roman Catholic diocese in north-western Ireland. It is one of eight suffragan dioceses that are subject to the Metropolitan Archdiocese of Armagh. Wikipedia
